{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment, lightly grease with non-stick spray and set aside.","Place cranberries into mixing bowl and chop <b>7 sec\/speed 7<b>, scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add pistachios and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place sugar and butter into mixing bowl and whip <b>1 min\/speed 3.5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 2 eggs and almond extract and mix <b>1 min\/speed 3.5<b>.","Add flour, reserved chopped cranberry-pistachio mixture, baking powder and salt and mix <b>1 min 30 sec\/\/speed 1<b>.","Transfer dough to prepared baking sheet and shape into a log (approx. 13 in. x 3 in.). In a small bowl whisk 1 egg. Brush top and sides of log with whisked egg and bake for 30-35 minutes (350°F). Remove tray from oven and let cool 1 hour. Meanwhile reduce oven temperature to 300°F.","Cut dough into ½ inch slices with a bread knife. Place onto baking sheet, cut side up, and bake for 15 minutes (300°F).","Flip biscotti over and bake a further 15 minutes (300°F). Allow to cool completely before serving or packaging for gift giving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["non-stick spray oil","2 oz dried cranberries","2 oz unsalted pistachios, shelled","6 oz sugar","2 oz unsalted butter, room temperature, diced","3 large eggs, divided","1 tsp almond extract","12 oz all-purpose flour","1 tsp baking powder","¼ tsp salt"]}],"id":"r421825","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-PsnKoOTr87U\/XZWYvNBOmcI\/AAAAAAAAeCk\/SV-n0uPP9JECbzRPlpXiKEpuPFUNvOLTACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_J8dVL-MeTZlXQpnc.png","title":"Pistachio Cranberry Biscotti","publishedAt":"2018-12-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"20 g","calories":"506 kJ \/ 121 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking sheet, parchment paper, bread knife, pastry brush, wire whisk, oven","basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h","25 pieces"]